Enums/JIRAProjectsExpandParameter.html#/.abstract: All project keys associated with the project.

Enums/JIRAIssueExpandParameter.html#/s:1.abstract: All possible transitions for the given issue

Enums/JIRAIssueExpandParameter.html#/s:1.name: operations
Enums/JIRAIssueExpandParameter.html#/s:1.abstract: All possibles operations available for the issue

Enums/JIRAIssueExpandParameter.html#/s:1.name: editmeta
Enums/JIRAIssueExpandParameter.html#/s:1.abstract: Information about how each field may be edited

Enums/JIRAIssueExpandParameter.html#/s:1.name: changelog
Enums/JIRAIssueExpandParameter.html#/s:1.abstract: A list of recent updates of an issue, sorted by date, starting from the newest

Enums/JIRAIssueExpandParameter.html#/s:1.name: versionedRepresentations
Enums/JIRAIssueExpandParameter.html#/s:1.abstract: REST representations of all fields. Some fields may have multiple versions. REST representations are numbered. The greatest number always represents the most recent version. It is recommended to always use the most recent version. Once expand=versionedRepresentations parameter is provided in the request then fields field is excluded from the response

Enums/JIRAIssueExpandParameter.html.name: JIRAIssueExpandParameter
Enums/JIRAIssueExpandParameter.html.abstract: Multi-value parameter defining the additional issue attributes to be included in the response. These attributes are not returned by default

Enums/JIRAFieldParameter.html.name: JIRAFieldParameter
Enums/JIRAFieldParameter.html.abstract: Multi-value parameter defining the fields returned for the issue. By default, all fields are returned

Enums/JIRAPropertyParameter.html.name: JIRAPropertyParameter
Enums/JIRAPropertyParameter.html.abstract: Multi-value parameter defining the list of properties returned for the issue. Unlike fields, properties are not included in the response by default. Similarly to fields you can specify particular properties to be included in the response or exclude some of them using a - (minus) sign

Enums/JIRAProjectsExpandParameter.html.name: JIRAProjectsExpandParameter
Enums/JIRAProjectsExpandParameter.html.abstract: Multi-value parameter defining request properties to expand in the response. These are not returned by default.

Enums/JIRAProjectExpandParameter.html.name: JIRAProjectExpandParameter
Enums/JIRAProjectExpandParameter.html.abstract: Multi-value parameter defining request properties to expand in the response. These are not returned by default.

Classes/JIRAProjectsController.html#/s:1.name: getAllProjects(expand:recent:completion:)
Classes/JIRAProjectsController.html#/s:1.abstract: Returns all projects visible for the currently logged in user, ie. all the projects the user has either ‘Browse projects’ or ‘Administer projects’ permission. If no user is logged in, it returns all projects that are visible for anonymous users.

Classes/JIRAProjectsController.html#/s:1.name: getProject(projectIdOrKey:expand:completion:)
Classes/JIRAProjectsController.html#/s:1.abstract: Returns a full representation of a single project.

Classes/JIRAIssuesController.html#/s:10S.abstract: Creates multiple issues or sub-tasks from a JSON representation, in a single bulk operation.

Classes/JIRAIssuesController.html#/s:10S.name: getIssue(issueIdOrKey:expand:fields:properties:fieldsByKeys:updateHistory:completion:)
Classes/JIRAIssuesController.html#/s:10S.abstract: Returns a full representation of the issue for the given issue key.

Classes/JIRAIssuesController.html#/s:10S.name: getTransitions(issueIdOrKey:transitionId:skipRemoteOnlyCondition:completion:)
Classes/JIRAIssuesController.html#/s:10S.abstract: Returns a list of transitions available for this issue for the current user.

Classes/JIRAIssuesController.html#/s:10S.name: getAllIssueTypes(completion:)
Classes/JIRAIssuesController.html#/s:10S.abstract: Returns a list of all issue types visible to the user
